      // Loyalty: -20 (20% of 100) = 170
      // Follow-up: -15 (15% of 170)? = 170 - 25.5 = 144.5. No.

      // What if follow-up is 15% of the base, not the remaining?
      // 100 + 50 + 30 = 180
      // Loyalty: -20 = 160
      // First insurance: +10 = 170
      // Follow-up: -15 (15% of 100) = 155. YES!

